          </p>
            <ul class="animate">
              <li>Privacy</li>
              <li>Homelabbing</li>
              <li>Activism</li>
              <li>Capitalism</li>
              <li>Running an Ethical Company</li>
              <li>Personal rants</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="animate">
            These all sound like varied topics that don't relate at all, which is true if you werent me. 
            All my endeavors have always been about pursuding people (I'll get into that in a more personal post later). The problem is that as our society becomes more and more attention focused (see Kyla Scanlon for more about the attention economy), we start to commodify 
            </p>
          <h2>Who am I to say I'm an expert at these topics</h2>
          <p class="animate">
            - This is a complex questionThis might not be for you.eserved for when i can afford my therapist
            - I'm funny (?)
            - I can confidently say I'm not an expert on these topics, but I will say, I will try my best to be as factual as I can
          </p>
            <h2>Why a lighthouse?</h2>
            <p class="animate">
              Why anonymous reader 
            </p>
